build.rs unconditionally passes -flto=thin (Clang ThinLTO, producing
LLVM-bitcode-only .o files) when compiling the vendored C/C++ submodules
(volk, parallel-rdp, simd compat, rcheevos) via the `cc` crate, and
doesn't emit the extra linker flags parallel-rdp/volk actually need on
this fork's GNU-binutils cross toolchain. Both are fixed together here
since they touch adjacent lines.

1. This fork's buildroot toolchain links with GNU binutils (ld/ar),
   which cannot index or link LLVM-bitcode objects - the final link
   fails with "libvolk.a: error adding symbols: archive has no index;
   run ranlib to add one" regardless of which `ar`/`ranlib` binary is
   explicitly configured, since no GNU-binutils `ar` can generate a
   symbol table for bitcode-only objects (only `llvm-ar` understands
   that format). Drop ThinLTO for these four translation units - a pure
   optimization, not a correctness requirement.

2. `-lvulkan`: parallel-rdp calls a handful of core (non-EXT) vk*
   functions directly rather than through volk's function-pointer
   indirection, needing an actual link-time libvulkan.

3. `--start-group`/`--end-group` around volk/parallel-rdp/
   retroachievements: cargo links these three vendored static libs in
   the same order build.rs's `.compile()` calls happen in (`-lvolk`
   before `-lparallel-rdp`), but libparallel-rdp.a's own objects are
   what reference volk's exported symbols (volkLoadInstance,
   volkInitializeCustom, the EXT/KHR extension trampolines volk.c
   defines) - GNU ld doesn't re-scan an already-processed static
   archive for a later, newly-discovered undefined symbol, so without
   grouping they stay unresolved.

Using `cargo:rustc-link-arg` (rather than a global RUSTFLAGS override in
the buildroot .mk) scopes these extra flags to just gopher64's own
binary link step - RUSTFLAGS is global to every crate rustc invokes in
the whole dependency graph and broke unrelated dependency crates that
build their own cdylib (e.g. sevenz-rust2) by handing them link args
pointing at libraries only gopher64's own build.rs OUT_DIR has.

--- a/build.rs
+++ b/build.rs
@@ -150,15 +150,17 @@
         println!("cargo:rustc-link-lib=dylib=freetype");
     }
 
-    volk_build.flag("-flto=thin");
-    rdp_build.flag("-flto=thin");
-    simd_build.flag("-flto=thin");
-    retroachievements_build.flag("-flto=thin");
-
     volk_build.compile("volk");
     rdp_build.compile("parallel-rdp");
     retroachievements_build.compile("retroachievements");
 
+    println!("cargo:rustc-link-arg=-lvulkan");
+    println!("cargo:rustc-link-arg=-Wl,--start-group");
+    println!("cargo:rustc-link-arg=-lvolk");
+    println!("cargo:rustc-link-arg=-lparallel-rdp");
+    println!("cargo:rustc-link-arg=-lretroachievements");
+    println!("cargo:rustc-link-arg=-Wl,--end-group");
+
     let out_path = std::path::PathBuf::from(std::env::var("OUT_DIR").unwrap());
 
     let mut retroachievements_builder = bindgen::Builder::default()
